SENORITA BROOKE vied for the lead early then settled back to stalk the pace down the late backstretch and throughout the turn, then dueled for the show prize down the lane and just missed in the end. MIZ JAMESON moved up along the inside while chasing the pace mid pack, then made a mild bid while three wide on the turn and was no threat. ELMO'S SECRET raced along the inside behind the pack and was no threat. BLUEGRASS DIXIE raced behind the field while two wide then faded throughout and was no menace.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HAILEY'S JEWEL unhurried early to be near the rear of the field the first half mile while saving ground along the fence, cut the corner turning for home, closed well tipping out around the pacesetter and finished with a flurry under strong handling. OLIVIA'S RACE DAY well placed just off the leaders to the head of the lane, loomed in upper stretch but was out-finished to the wire. SI QUERE slow early to trail to the quarter pole, angled wide in upper stretch and closed well belatedly. KAUSE I'M DEVINE reserved off the pace to the far turn and made a mild bid down the lane. TRANQUILITY raced near the rear of the field most of the way and passed tiring rivals down the stretch. COUNTRY JEWEL went evenly never posing a threat. HEAD OVER BOOTS prompted the pace for a half mile and gave way coming home. LUMBERJACK LESLIE showed brief speed to be prominent in the first turn and was through early. BLING ON THE LIGHT stalked the pace to the far turn and tired.
